content: Great app! I would give it a five stars but there are a few items that would certainly help being improved. The gap however is the narrator, which I'm assuming is AI, pauses and the reading is not fluid, it's choppy and inconsistent. Secondly, when you share something that you've looked up, it puts it all in one paragraph. I'd like to see it shared exactly how it's visible in the actual app. With appropriate spacing and consistent numbering.

It's Impressive but it cuts off midway fulfilling an instruction with an Error Message. The Copy Function also has a bug that Lumps All the words together, thereby Scattering the organised Itemised or intented Organization of the original output in the App. E.g 1. Read 2. Think 3. Speak When Copied, it becomes: 1.Read2.Think3.Speak Thereby frustrating the user, as all the time gained via a quick response, would be lost in rearranging the lumped up Text.
